  <front>
   <head>HUMAN PLEASURE OR PAIN.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">WHEN clouds and rain deform the sky,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And light'nings glare around,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Amidst the dreary, cheerless scene,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Some comfort may be found.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">There will, at some far-distant spot,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">A streak of light appear,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Or, when the sullen vapours break,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">The ether will be clear.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And if the sun illumes the east,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And sheds his gladsome ray,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Some boding mist, or passing cloud</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Will threat the rising day.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The heart rejoicing in the view,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And dancing with delight,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Oft feels the touch of palsied fear,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And sinks at thought of night.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">So Hope's bright torch more clearly shines,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Amidst surrounding gloom,</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And, beldame Fortune vainly throws</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Her mantle o'er the tomb.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
